gov.nasa.larcfm.IO

Class ConfigReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nasa.larcfm.IO.ConfigReader
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ErrorReporter, ParameterProvider, ParameterReader

    public final class ConfigReader
extends java.lang.Object
implements ParameterReader, ParameterProvider, ErrorReporter
    This object will read in and store a set of configuration parameters. The parameters can be listed in the conventional way, such as: param = 10 [NM]. In addition, the parameters can be listed in a table format:
    param1 param2 param3 1 5 100 2 10 99 3 20 98 4 10 97 5 5 96 If the parameters are stored in this way, then every call to the "next()" method will update the parameters (for this example, the parameters: param1, param2, and param3) with the next values in the file.

    Instead of next(), the nextIterate() method can be called which will return all of the param1 values with each of the param2 values, and so on. In this case the parameters may require different numbers of values; so, the columns of values should be augmented with an invalid value that will be ignored, for example param1 param2 param3 1 5 100 2 10 99 3 20 x 4 x x 5 x x includeConfigFile: A special set parameters will be stripped and processed immediately. Parameters starting with the string "includeConfigFile" will launch a temporary ConfigReader that will recursively attempt to read any parameters in the indicated file and add them it this reader. Parameters read from secondary files will not overwrite parameters set in their parent files.
